Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
gui_highlight_safety_mechanism(25.10)    gui_highlight_safety_mechanism(25.10)

Name
       gui_highlight_safety_mechanism  -  Highlights  safety-related instances
       and groups based on the specified parameters

Syntax
       gui_highlight_safety_mechanism

       [-help]

       {[-dcls {insts nets_internal nets_interface nets_common nets_top}

         | -tmr {parents clones voters}

         | -ser {insts}]}

       [-color <string> | -auto_color ]

       [-group <group_name>

         [-exclusive_groups ]]

       [-dcls {insts nets_internal nets_interface nets_common nets_top}

         [-group <group_name>]]

       [-tmr {parents clones voters}

         [-inst <inst_name>]]

       Highlights safety-related instances and groups based on  the  specified
       parameters.  One,  and  only  one,  of the following parameters must be
       specified with the command, depending on whether you want to  highlight
       the  safety  features  of Dual Core Lock Step (DCLS) groups, Soft Error
       Resilience (SER) instances, or  Triple  Modular  Redundancy  (TMR)  in-
       stances:

              * -dcls

              * -ser

              * -tmr

       The gui_highlight_safety_mechanism command can be used only after a USF
       file  has been loaded. If this command is run before the safety flow is
       enabled, the tool gives the following error:

       **ERROR: (IMPGUI-3009): The safety flow is not enabled

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the gui_highlight_safety_mechanism
              command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man  command:
              man gui_highlight_safety_mechanism.

       -auto_color
              Specifies  that  the highlight colors should be picked automati-
              cally.

              If -auto_color is specified with -dcls, the tool:

              * Highlights the instances, internal nets, and interface nets of
                a single group in the same color.

              * Uses a different color for every group and for  top-level  and
                common nets.

              If -auto_color is specified with -tmr, the tool:

              * Highlights all parents in the same color.

              * Highlights all clones in a second color.

              * Highlights all voters in a third color.

              If neither -auto_color nor -color is specified, the tool behaves
              as if -auto_color is specified.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -color <color_name>
              Specifies  the  color  to be used for highlighting the specified
              safety mechanisms.

              If -color is not specified, the tool picks a  random  color  for
              highlighting.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -dcls {insts nets_internal nets_interface nets_common nets_top}
              Highlights  the instances and nets of DCLS groups, as specified.
              You can specify one or more  of  the  following  arguments  with
              -dcls:

              * insts  - Highlights the group region in the Floorplan view and
                its instances in the Physical view:

                * If -group is not specified, highlights all the  DCLS  groups
                  in the design.

                * If  -group  is  specified,  highlights  only  that specified
                  group.

              * nets_internal - Highlights the internal nets:

                * If -group is not specified, highlights the internal nets  of
                  all the DCLS groups in the design.

                * If -group is specified, highlights the internal nets of only
                  that specified group.

              * nets_interface - Highlights the interface nets:

                * If -group is not specified, highlights the interface nets of
                  all the DCLS groups in the design.

                * If  -group  is  specified, highlights the interface  nets of
                  only that specified group.

              * nets_common - Highlights the common nets:

                * If -group is not specified, highlights the  common  nets  of
                  all the DCLS groups in the design.

                * If  -group  is specified, highlights the common nets of only
                  that specified group.

              * nets_top - Highlights all the top nets:

                * This argument is valid only if -group is not specified.

              The -tmr and -ser parameters are mutually exclusive with -dcls.

              Data_type: enum_list, required

       -exclusive_groups
              Highlights the safety features of the exclusive  groups  of  the
              DCLS  group  specified with -group. The same safety features are
              highlighted for both the group specified with -group and for its
              exclusive groups. For example, if -dcls {insts nets_internal} is
              specified with -group group_A1,  the  tool  highlights  the  in-
              stances and internal nets of group_A1 and its exclusive groups.

              This option is valid only if -dcls and -group are specified.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -group <group_name>
              Highlights the safety features of only the specified DCLS group.

              This  option  is  valid  only if -dcls is specified. If -dcls is
              specified without -group, the tool highlights  the  features  of
              all the DCLS groups in the design.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -inst <inst_name>
              Highlights  the  safety  features  of only the specified TMR in-
              stance.

              This option is valid only if -tmr is specified. If -tmr is spec-
              ified without -inst, the tool highlights the features of all the
              TMR instances.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -ser {insts}
              Highlights all SER instances.

              Data_type: enum, required

       -tmr {parents clones voters}
              Highlights TMR parents, clones, or voters,  as  specified.   You
              can specify one or more of the following arguments with -tmr:

              * parents - Highlights TMR parents:

                * If -inst is not specified, highlights all the TMR parents.

                * If  -inst is specified, highlights only the TMR parent asso-
                  ciated with the specified instance.

              * clones - Highlights TMR clones:

                * If -inst is not specified, highlights all the TMR clones.

                * If -inst is specified, highlights only the TMR clones  asso-
                  ciated with the specified instance.

              * voters - Highlights TMR voters:

                * If -inst is not specified, highlights all the TMR voters.

                * If  -inst is specified, highlights only the TMR voters asso-
                  ciated with the specified instance.

              Data_type: enum_list, required

Examples
              * The following command highlights all DCLS groups in red:

                gui_highlight_safety_mechanism -dcls {insts} -color red

              * The following command highlights the internal nets of  group_A
                in blue:

                gui_highlight_safety_mechanism  -group group_A -dcls {nets_in-
                ternal} -color blue

              * The following command highlights the instances and routing  of
                group_A and that of its exclusive group, group_B, in different
                colors:

                gui_highlight_safety_mechanism  -group  group_A  -dcls  {insts
                nets_internal nets_interface} -exclusive_groups -auto_color

              * The following command highlights all TMR parent flops  in  the
                design in red:

                gui_highlight_safety_mechanism -tmr {parents} -color red

              * The  following command highlights all TMR parents, clones, and
                voting logic in the design in different colors:

                gui_highlight_safety_mechanism -tmr  {parents  clones  voters}
                -auto_color

              * The  following  command  highlights all clones of the tmr_inst
                instance in blue:

                gui_highlight_safety_mechanism -inst  tmr_inst  -tmr  {clones}
                -color blue

